(5\;\text{choose}\, 2, 2, 1)
\displaystyle \binom{n}{k_1, k_2..., k_m} = \dfrac{n!}{k_1! \times k_2! \times \cdots \times k_m!}
\binom{5}{2, 2, 1} = \frac{5!}{2!\,2!\,1!} = \dfrac{120}{2\cdot 2 \cdot 1} = \dfrac{120}{4} = 30
n,\,
n\,! = n(n-1)(n-2)\cdots(2)(1)
\frac{5!}{2!2!1!}
{n\choose{k_1, k_2, ..., k_m}}=\frac{n!}{k_1!\times k_2!\times...\times k_m!}
